    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-09-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-10-05T18:22:27Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to expand the eligibility of certain small insurance companies (other than life insurance companies) for the alternative corporate income tax by increasing the premium limitation used to determine such eligibility to $1.971 million (from $1.2 million), with an annual inflation adjustment to that increased amount after 2007.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
